# Interactive FAQ Webpage (OOP in JavaScript)

## 📌 Project Description

This project is an interactive FAQ webpage where users can click on questions to view or hide answers. It is built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript with Object-Oriented Programming concepts.

## 🚀 Features

* Toggle answers on click
* Smooth expand/collapse animation
* Dynamic rendering using JavaScript
* OOP-based structure using class `QAItem`
* Clean and responsive UI

## 🧠 Concepts Used

* DOM Manipulation
* Event Handling
* JavaScript Classes (OOP)
* CSS Transitions
* Dynamic Content Rendering

## 📂 Project Structure

* `index.html` → Structure of webpage
* `style.css` → Styling and animations
* `script.js` → Logic using OOP

## ⚙️ How It Works

* Each FAQ item is created using a `QAItem` class
* Questions are clickable
* Clicking toggles visibility of answers
* Icons (+ / -) update dynamically

## 📌 Conclusion

This project demonstrates the use of Object-Oriented Programming in JavaScript along with interactive UI design.
